"{\"uid\": \"politifact.com-article-2024-aug-02-claims-about-algerian-boxer-imane-khelifs-olympic\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Our only agenda is to publish the truth so you can be an informed participant in democracy.We need your help.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 109, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More Info  Algeria's Imane Khelif, left, fights Italy's Angela Carini in their women's 66kg preliminary boxing match at the 2024 Summer Olympics, Thursday, Aug. 1, 2024, in Paris, France.\", \"from\": 111, \"to\": 298, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 122, \"end\": 129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999999931560524, \"rank\": 6.530261019800811e-09, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 132, \"end\": 144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}, {\"begin\": 159, \"end\": 164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.7459665462951354, \"rank\": 0.3405105388005897, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 167, \"end\": 180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\", \"score\": 0.9999962103660394, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Angela Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\"}, {\"begin\": 284, \"end\": 289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.5636344479786166e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 291, \"end\": 297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8373555147750362, \"rank\": 0.19403242859912595, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(AP)  The Boxing Unit set up by the International Olympic Committee, which handles eligibility for boxing at the 2024 Paris Olympics, has affirmed the eligibility of Algerian boxer Imane Khelif and Taiwanese boxer Lin Yu-ting.\", \"from\": 299, \"to\": 525, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 300, \"end\": 302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.422061517796551e-24, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}, {\"begin\": 309, \"end\": 315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8508700777195177e-17, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}, {\"begin\": 335, \"end\": 366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 465, \"end\": 473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999998475586952, \"rank\": 1.5138132286048073e-07, \"text\": \"Algerian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 480, \"end\": 492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}, {\"begin\": 497, \"end\": 506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Taipei\", \"score\": 0.9999997555310373, \"rank\": 2.4373635436131937e-07, \"text\": \"Taiwanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Taipei\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Taipei\"}, {\"begin\": 513, \"end\": 524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lin Yu-ting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Russian-led International Boxing Association disqualified the two athletes from the 2023 World Championships, saying they failed to meet the eligibility requirements to compete in women's sports.\", \"from\": 527, \"to\": 726, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Olympic Committee no longer recognizes the International Boxing Association, however.\", \"from\": 727, \"to\": 830, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 731, \"end\": 762, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 788, \"end\": 820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0900423244780467e-31, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"International Olympic Committee spokesperson Mark Adams said Aug. 2 that Khelif \\\"was born female, was registered female, lived her life as a female, boxed as a female, has a female passport.\\\"\", \"from\": 832, \"to\": 1023, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 832, \"end\": 863, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 877, \"end\": 887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Adams_(basketball,_born_May_1956)\", \"score\": 0.5137413298826524, \"rank\": 0.45833333333321225, \"text\": \"Mark Adams\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Adams_(basketball,_born_May_1956)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Adams_(basketball,_born_May_1956)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Algerian boxer Imane Khelif has fought in the boxing ring for years, but now she is facing jabs of another kind: those questioning her gender.\", \"from\": 1025, \"to\": 1167, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1025, \"end\": 1033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999998475586952, \"rank\": 1.5138132286048073e-07, \"text\": \"Algerian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 1040, \"end\": 1052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some people are wondering whether she should be competing in the Olympics at all.\", \"from\": 1168, \"to\": 1249, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Khelif's performance at the 2024 Olympics has become a flashpoint in the discourse about allowing transgender athletes to compete in sports.\", \"from\": 1251, \"to\": 1391, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Beating women is now a spectator sport,\\\" aJuly 30 post's textread.\", \"from\": 1393, \"to\": 1460, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Why are the #Olympics allowing this male to enter the boxing ring with a woman?\\\"\", \"from\": 1461, \"to\": 1542, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Imagine training your whole life, making (it) to the Olympics just to get your dreams literally smashed by some men!\\\"\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1662, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"the caption said.\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1680, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Enough is enough.\\\"\", \"from\": 1681, \"to\": 1700, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Khelif of Algeria and Lin Yu-ting of Taiwan have been deemed eligible to participate in women's boxing in the Paris Olympics, a decision that has drawn controversy and speculation, particularly after Italian boxer Angela Carini quit in a Thursday bout against Khelifafter 46 seconds.\", \"from\": 1702, \"to\": 1985, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1712, \"end\": 1719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999999931560524, \"rank\": 6.530261019800811e-09, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 1724, \"end\": 1735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lin Yu-ting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\"}, {\"begin\": 1739, \"end\": 1745, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9999998159310223, \"rank\": 1.8402779532771078e-07, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 1902, \"end\": 1909, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.8120087929422675, \"rank\": 0.23088126857398103, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1916, \"end\": 1929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\", \"score\": 0.9999962103660394, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Angela Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Social media users claimed that Khelif was a man because she was disqualified in a previous tournament.Russian state-controlled mediaquoted the president of the disqualifying boxing organization saying the results of a DNA test showed Khelif has XY chromosomes.\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 2248, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Biological femalestypicallyhave two X chromosomes (XX) and biological males typically have one X and one Y chromosome (XY).\", \"from\": 2249, \"to\": 2372, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2300, \"end\": 2302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4626373858093908e-19, \"text\": \"XX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\"}, {\"begin\": 2368, \"end\": 2370, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"score\": 0.9999995312820108, \"rank\": 4.6871837528255025e-07, \"text\": \"XY\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Public figures such asformer President Donald Trump,X owner Elon Muskandauthor J.K. Rowlingamplified the claims that Khelif is a man.\", \"from\": 2374, \"to\": 2507, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2413, \"end\": 2425, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999495712485, \"rank\": 5.042764317504458e-08, \"text\": \"Donald Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But those claims lack context about Olympics eligibility requirements, the circumstances of Khelif's and Lin's previous disqualifications and the lack of information surrounding the DNA tests the International Boxing Association said it administered.\", \"from\": 2509, \"to\": 2759, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2705, \"end\": 2737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0900423244780467e-31, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The claims that Khelif is not a woman are not substantiated.\", \"from\": 2761, \"to\": 2821, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Khelif has always competedas a woman; she has never come out as transgender or intersex.\", \"from\": 2822, \"to\": 2910, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Algerian boxer was born female, was registered female, lived her life as a female, boxed as a female, has a female passport,\\\" International Olympic Committee spokesperson Mark Adamssaidin a Aug. 2 media briefing (14:34).\", \"from\": 2911, \"to\": 3136, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2916, \"end\": 2924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999998475586952, \"rank\": 1.5138132286048073e-07, \"text\": \"Algerian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 3042, \"end\": 3073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is not a transgender case.\\\"\", \"from\": 3137, \"to\": 3170, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Scientifically, this is not a man fighting a woman,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 3172, \"to\": 3234, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Algeria's Olympic Committee denounced the attacks against Khelif in anAug.\", \"from\": 3236, \"to\": 3310, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3236, \"end\": 3243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999999931560524, \"rank\": 6.530261019800811e-09, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"1 statement, calling them \\\"malicious and unethical.\\\"\", \"from\": 3311, \"to\": 3363, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"These attempts at defamation, based on lies, are totally unfair, especially at a crucial time when she is preparing for the Olympic Games, the peak of her career.\", \"from\": 3365, \"to\": 3528, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The COA (Le Comit\\u00e9 Olympique et Sportif Alg\\u00e9rien) has taken all necessary measures to protect our champion,\\\" the statement read.\", \"from\": 3529, \"to\": 3657, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3533, \"end\": 3536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7018260553831014e-27, \"text\": \"COA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Taiwanese President Lai Ching-te's spokespersonsupportedLin in an Aug. 1, X post.\", \"from\": 3659, \"to\": 3740, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Khelif and Lin were disqualified at the 2023 Women's World Boxing Championships in New Delhi after they failed an eligibility test.\", \"from\": 3742, \"to\": 3873, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3825, \"end\": 3834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Delhi\", \"score\": 0.9999881120276716, \"rank\": 1.1888113482032626e-05, \"text\": \"New Delhi\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Delhi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Delhi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Russian-led International Boxing Association, which organized the World Championships, said DNA tests showed the two athleteshad XY chromosomes, according to a March 2023 statement from the president to Russian news agency Tass.\", \"from\": 3875, \"to\": 4107, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3891, \"end\": 3923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0900423244780467e-31, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 4082, \"end\": 4106, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Russian news agency Tass\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\"}, {\"begin\": 4082, \"end\": 4106, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Russian news agency Tass\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the International Boxing Association does not oversee qualification for the 2024 Olympics; the Paris 2024 Boxing Unit, set up by the International Olympic Committee, does.\", \"from\": 4108, \"to\": 4283, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4116, \"end\": 4148, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0900423244780467e-31, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 4207, \"end\": 4217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.086778062506107e-27, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 4218, \"end\": 4224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8508700777195177e-17, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}, {\"begin\": 4245, \"end\": 4276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Boxing Association wasstripped of its Olympic recognitionin 2023, because of adisputeinvolving its management, its finances and its judging integrity.\", \"from\": 4285, \"to\": 4453, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4289, \"end\": 4321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0900423244780467e-31, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In anAug.\", \"from\": 4454, \"to\": 4463, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"1 statement, the International Olympic Committee reiterated that the gender and age of athletes competing in boxing are based on their passports, as it has been with previous Olympics and with tournaments during the qualification period during 2023 and 2024.\", \"from\": 4464, \"to\": 4722, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4481, \"end\": 4512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have seen in reports misleading information about two female athletes competing at the Olympic Games Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 4724, \"to\": 4840, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The two athletes have been competing in international boxing competitions for many years in the women's category,\\\" the statement read.\", \"from\": 4841, \"to\": 4975, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"These two athletes were the victims of a sudden and arbitrary decision by the IBA.\", \"from\": 4976, \"to\": 5059, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5055, \"end\": 5058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.6564668184666358, \"rank\": 0.5233062385927322, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Towards the end of the IBA World Championships in 2023, they were suddenly disqualified without any due process.\\\"\", \"from\": 5060, \"to\": 5173, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The statement named neither Khelif nor Lin, but Adams read out that statement in anAug.\", \"from\": 5175, \"to\": 5262, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"2 press conferencewhile fielding questions about the two athletes.\", \"from\": 5263, \"to\": 5329, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Both Khelif and Lincompeted in the 2020 Olympicsin Tokyo.\", \"from\": 5331, \"to\": 5388, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Eligibility standardsfor boxing in the 2024 Paris Olympics are determined by an ad hoc unit the International Olympic Committee set up after it stopped recognizing the International Boxing Association.\", \"from\": 5390, \"to\": 5591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5486, \"end\": 5517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 5558, \"end\": 5590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0900423244780467e-31, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Boxing Association appealed the committee's decision, but the Court of Arbitration for Sportdismissed the appeal, saying the association did not improve financial transparency and sustainability, has not ensured its integrity by changing its process involving referees and judges and has not reformed its governance.\", \"from\": 5593, \"to\": 5927, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5597, \"end\": 5629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0900423244780467e-31, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In aJuly 31 statementaddressing the controversy, the International Boxing Association said Khelif and Lin \\\"did not undergo a testosterone examination but were subject to a separate and recognized test, whereby the specifics remain confidential.\\\"\", \"from\": 5929, \"to\": 6174, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5982, \"end\": 6014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0900423244780467e-31, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The test, it said, showed the athletes have \\\"competitive advantages over other female competitors.\\\"\", \"from\": 6175, \"to\": 6274, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Boxing Association's board of directors meetingminutesfrom March 25, 2023, said that the board asked why the disqualification of the two athletes was being raisedat the end of the championshipsafter they had already gone through different tournament stages.\", \"from\": 6276, \"to\": 6551, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6280, \"end\": 6312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0900423244780467e-31, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Boxing Association's secretary general and CEO, \\\"acting on behalf of IBA,\\\" told the two athletes about their disqualification.\", \"from\": 6552, \"to\": 6696, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6556, \"end\": 6588, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0900423244780467e-31, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 6639, \"end\": 6642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.6564668184666358, \"rank\": 0.5233062385927322, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Khelif's Olympics profilepreviously saidshe was disqualified \\\"just hours before her gold medal showdown\\\" against a Chinese opponent.\", \"from\": 6698, \"to\": 6830, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6813, \"end\": 6820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9674541382213976, \"rank\": 0.03363289805777171, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the time, Khelif called the disqualification a \\\"big conspiracy.\\\"\", \"from\": 6832, \"to\": 6899, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lindid not appealthe disqualification; Khelif took her case to the Court of Arbitration for Sport, anindependent institutionthat arbitrates sports-related disputes, but later withdrew it.\", \"from\": 6900, \"to\": 7087, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"RELATED:Tuberville's claim that Olympics decided 'men can box women' misses the mark  Instagram post(archived), July 30, 2024  Truth Social post by former President Donald Trump, Aug. 1, 2024  X post by Elon Musk, Aug. 1, 2024  X post by J.K. Rowling, Aug. 1, 2024  Algerian Olympic and Sports Committee,COA denounces attacks against athlete Imane Khelif(translated by Google), Aug. 1, 2024  YouTube video by IOC Media,Paris 2024 - IOC Daily Briefing 02.08.2024, Aug. 2, 2024  X post by the Taiwan Presidential Office Spokesperson, Aug. 1, 2024  The New York Times,Italian Boxer Quits Bout, Sparking Furor Over Gender at Olympics, Aug. 1, 2024  Time,What to Know About the Gender Fight in Olympic Boxing, Aug. 1, 2024  Wired,The Shameful Controversy Over Olympic Boxer Imane Khelif, Aug. 1, 2024  Tass,IBA bans athletes from world championships for trying to pass themselves off as women(translated by Google), March 25, 2023  National Human Genome Research Institute,Human Genomic Variation fact sheet, accessed Aug 1.\", \"from\": 7089, \"to\": 8108, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7097, \"end\": 7107,